OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F345A1784306880
OL,3,CStaffordshire residents warned about
OL,4,Ctoxic algae in country park water
OL,6,FIt looks like green or turquoise wispy
OL,7,Fpaint or scum on the water's surface
OL,8,Fand naturally occurs in lakes, ponds,
OL,9,Fand rivers.
OL,11,FHayley Coles, Staffordshire County
OL,12,FCouncil's Deputy Leader and Cabinet
OL,13,FMember for Communities and Culture,
OL,14,Fsaid:
OL,16,F"We've identified blue-green algae at
OL,17,Fboth Chasewater and Cannock Chase, so
OL,18,Fwe're asking everyone to stay well
OL,19,Faway from the affected water for their
OL,20,Fown safety.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G2/3
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,346,340,120,260,000,100
PN,34503
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F345A1784306880
OL,3,CStaffordshire residents warned about
OL,4,Ctoxic algae in country park water
OL,6,F"Please don't let children enter the
OL,7,Fwater and keep dogs on leads near
OL,8,Faffected areas.
OL,10,F"Dogs should never be allowed to swim
OL,11,Fin or drink from water containing blue-
OL,12,Fgreen algae, as it can be fatal.
OL,14,F"Warning signs have been put in place
OL,15,Fbut, if you think you or your pet has
OL,16,Fcome into contact with blue-green
OL,17,Falgae, seek medical or veterinary
OL,18,Fadvice straight away."
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G3/3
